++ Application Independent State

APS is [Data] that is not specific to any particular application. APS are representations that can be utilized by any application.
    * ApplicationState

Examples of APS include:
    * URL
    * Position - time into a video

++Architecture

[Applications] specify what APS they can accept.
    * Web browsers will accept URL addresses
    * media applications accept the position.

APS is especially important when [Errors] occur and the application crashes. [Users] are given the choice to:
    * open again in the same application
    * open in a different application
    * save the ABS

